solution: ```java
class Solution {
    public int[] constructRectangle(int area) {
        int w = (int)Math.sqrt(area);
        while (area % w != 0) {
            w--;
        }
        return new int[]{area / w, w};
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(area))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Start with the integer closest to the square root of the area (the most balanced possible width) and decrement until the width divides the area evenly. This yields the pair [L, W] with the smallest difference while satisfying L ≥ W.

